-- Chandler, Lopez, Rondo Join U.S. Men's Basketball Team for London Olympics
-- Mason Levinson
-- 2010-07-15T16:53:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/chandler-lopez-rondo-join-u-s-men-s-basketball-team-for-london-olympics.html

          
          
             Guard  Rajon Rondo  and centers  Tyson Chandler  and  Robin Lopez  were added to the 2010-12 USA
Basketball men’s national team.  
 The addition of the three National Basketball Association
players increases the team’s roster to 24, USA Basketball said
in a  news release .  
 Chandler, who joined the Dallas Mavericks in a July 13
trade from the Charlotte Bobcats, as well as the Phoenix Suns’
Lopez and Boston Celtics’ Rondo are expected to be among 21
players actively participating in the team’s July 19-24 training
camp in Las Vegas.  
 USA Basketball will use the national team roster to select
the squads that will play in this year’s world championships and
the 2012 London Olympics. The  world championships  will be held
in Turkey from Aug. 28 through Sept. 12.  
